>[Question]
>Various sources, including my textbook (by Larson, Hostetler, and 
>Edwards) says that sigma depends on epsilon.  I thought it should be 
>the other way around, since it seems like I should "set" my sigma 
>first, which is on the x axis, the axis w/independent variables.  Why 
>does sigma depend on the epsilon value?  And also, why does the text 
>keep talking about how epsilon and sigma both have to be greater than 
>zero?    
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
